    "text": "(1) Stagg Street, at the N.E. corner of Manhattan Ave., showing the razing of old buildings, to make way for modern living quarters. At the extreme left, the white building is the Bushwick Savings Bank, on Graham Ave., and Grand Street; to the right, the building with the steeple is St. John's Evang. Lutheran Church on Maujer Street.\n\nMarch 5, 1936.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n\n(2) The same, showing in the background from left to right, St. Catherine's Hospital and P.S. No. 36 on the east side of Buswick Ave.\n\nMarch 31, 1936.\n\nP. L. Sperr.\n",
